<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1375,1546]" box="[151,554,1375,1402]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<heading box="[151,554,1375,1402]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" reason="5">
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith, 1874)" authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[151,554,1375,1402]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,391,1375,1402]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Pamphilius venustus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, F." box="[406,546,1375,1401]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="373 - 409" refId="ref79508" refString="Smith, F. (1874) Descriptions of new species of Tenthredinidae, Ichneumonidae, Chrysididae, Formicidae &amp; c. of Japan. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London for the Year, 1874, 373 - 409. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1874. tb 00867. x" type="journal article" year="1874">Smith, 1874</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,1375,1546]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
For the distribution of this species, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[552,748,1411,1437]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov (2017)</bibRefCitation>
noted “ 
<collectingCountry box="[836,917,1411,1437]" name="Russia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Russia</collectingCountry>
: FE (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[976,1181,1411,1437]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="179 - 197" refId="ref76388" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 b) Pamphilius stramineipes (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) and its close relatives. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 14, 179 - 197." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara, 1988b</bibRefCitation>
)”, apparently referring to 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[180,401,1447,1473]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="179 - 197" refId="ref76388" refString="Shinohara, A. (1988 b) Pamphilius stramineipes (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae) and its close relatives. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A, 14, 179 - 197." type="journal article" year="1988">Shinohara’s (1988b</bibRefCitation>
, P. 180) statement, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Smith)" authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[631,847,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[631,754,1448,1473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. venustus</emphasis>
(Smith)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Matsumura)" baseAuthorityName="Matsumura" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[901,1214,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sapporensis">
<emphasis box="[901,1062,1448,1473]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">P. sapporensis</emphasis>
(Matsumura)
</taxonomicName>
from the Far East”. 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N." box="[151,348,1483,1509]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="20 - 117" refId="ref79858" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. (2017) Suborder Symphyta - Sawflies and wood wasps. In: Lelej, A. S., Proshchalykin, M. Yu. &amp; Loktionov, V. M. (Eds.), Annotated catalogue of the Hymenoptera of Russia. Vol. I. Symphyta and Apocrita: Aculeata. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Supplement 6, pp. 20 - 117." type="journal article" year="2017">Sundukov (2017)</bibRefCitation>
seems to have misunderstood “the Far East”, which is much wider than “the Russian Far East”. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="NSMT" baseAuthorityName="Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[151,382,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[151,382,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Pamphilius venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[616,680,1520,1546]" name="Japan" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Japan</collectingCountry>
(Shinohara 2019, 2020).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
